# 🎯 Agentic RAG Pipeline with Deterministic Guardrails

![Python](https://img.shields.io/badge/Python-3.10-blue.svg)
![LangGraph](https://img.shields.io/badge/Orchestration-LangGraph-orange.svg)
![Groq](https://img.shields.io/badge/Inference-Groq_LPU-black.svg)
![Ragas](https://img.shields.io/badge/Evaluation-RAGAS-green.svg)

An enterprise-grade, stateful AI architecture designed to mitigate hallucinations and prompt injections in Large Language Models (LLMs). This project upgrades a standard Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) system into an **Agentic Workflow** using LangGraph, secured by deterministic low-temperature guardrails.

## 📖 Project Overview

While LLMs excel at natural language generation, their enterprise adoption is often hindered by hallucinations and a lack of predictable reliability. This project provides a comprehensive, quantitatively evaluated blueprint for deploying secure AI agents.

**Core Objectives Achieved:**
1. Built a highly efficient **FAISS Vector Database** for localized context retrieval.
2. Engineered a stateful **LangGraph pipeline** for autonomous workflow routing.
3. Implemented a **Deterministic LLM Guardrail Node** to block adversarial prompt injections and off-topic queries.
4. Quantitatively verified the system's accuracy and safety using the **RAGAS framework** and a 70-Billion parameter judge model.

## ✨ Key Features

* **Agentic Orchestration:** Utilizes LangGraph to manage conversation state and intelligently route queries based on logical conditions rather than passive generation.
* **Security First:** A dedicated Guardrail Node (running Meta Llama 3.1 at `temperature=0`) intercepts and evaluates prompts *before* they reach the retrieval phase.
* **Ultra-Low Latency:** Powered by the Groq LPU API, ensuring that the additional guardrail and routing nodes do not compromise real-time user experience.
* **Automated CI/CD Evaluation:** Integrated GitHub Actions workflow to automatically run RAGAS spectrometer tests on every code push.
* **Interactive Dashboard:** Built-in Streamlit web application to visualize context precision, recall, faithfulness, and correctness metrics.

## 🛠️ Technology Stack

| Component | Technology | Purpose |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **Orchestration** | LangGraph | Stateful workflow management and conditional routing. |
| **Inference Engine** | Groq API | High-speed model execution. |
| **Core LLM** | Llama 3.1 (8B) | Guardrail decision-making and final response generation. |
| **Vector Store** | FAISS | In-memory similarity search and chunk retrieval. |
| **Embeddings** | HuggingFace | `all-MiniLM-L6-v2` for local, lightweight vectorization. |
| **Evaluation** | RAGAS (v0.1.22) | Quantitative assessment of AI output accuracy. |
| **Evaluation Judge**| Llama 3.3 (70B) | High-parameter impartial grading. |
| **Visualization** | Streamlit | Real-time reporting dashboard. |

## 📊 Evaluation Metrics

The system was rigorously tested against a manually verified Golden Dataset. The RAGAS framework provided the following baseline metrics, proving high accuracy and strict adherence to retrieved context:

* **Answer Correctness:** `0.8189` (81.9%)
* **Faithfulness (Hallucination Check):** `0.6667` (66.7%)
* **Context Precision:** `1.0000` (100%)
* **Context Recall:** `1.0000` (100%)

